So, for $5$ consecutive integer, let the integers be x−2,x−1,x,x+1,x+2. Then, by the definition of \textit{average}, we have\begin{align*}\textit{average}&=\frac{(x+2)+(x+1)+x+(x-1)+(x-2)}{5} \\ &=\frac{5x}{5} \\ &=x\end{align*}
As the average (mean) of these $5$ consecutive integers is $21,$ we have $x=21.$ Thus, the five consecutive integers are 19,20,21,22, and 23.< /think> <answer> The smallest of the five integers is $19.$</answer>

